## Steps

### step 1
id: open-command-palette
instruction: From anywhere in Altair, press Cmd+K (Mac) or Ctrl+K (Windows) to open the command palette.
success_criteria: A search box appears in the center of the screen labeled "Search..." or "Go to..." with suggestions below it.
anchor: "command palette"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Press Cmd+K on Mac or Ctrl+K on Windows. It opens immediately from any page.

### step 2
id: type-search-query
instruction: Type what you're looking for — a page name (Batches, Payments, Prior Auth), a patient name, an encounter number, a payer name, or a feature name (Denials, Memory, Scrub Rules). Results update in real-time.
success_criteria: Matching results appear below showing pages, patients, encounters, or features.
anchor: "search box"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Start typing anything. Results appear as you type.

### step 3
id: select-result
instruction: Click a result or use the arrow keys to highlight it and press Enter to navigate there.
success_criteria: The command palette closes and you are now on the selected screen or record.
anchor: "result"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click on any result in the list.

## Completion Message
that's the fastest way to jump anywhere in altair without clicking through the sidebar. use it whenever you need to find a patient, batch, or feature quickly.

